I realize I already gave you my blessing on this,
clark, and I don't want to lie to you.

48
00:05:09,222 --> 00:05:11,482
This whole thing
makes me feel uneasy.

49
00:05:11,515 --> 00:05:14,201
Dad, we've been watching met U.
Football games since I can remember.

50
00:05:14,279 --> 00:05:15,526
Now they're knocking on my door.

51
00:05:15,587 --> 00:05:17,997
I know that, and I'm proud of you for it.

52
00:05:18,047 --> 00:05:21,177
Then why can't I have a shot at what every other
high school kid dreams of?

53
00:05:21,227 --> 00:05:23,487
Because you're not like every
other high school kid, clark.

54
00:05:23,537 --> 00:05:24,842
On that field I am.

55
00:05:24,876 --> 00:05:28,709
I'm not even using my abilities... and I can be
the new starting quarterback for the metropolis bulldogs.

56
00:05:28,764 --> 00:05:31,861
There's gonna be millions of eyes on you.
You're gonna be under a magnifying glass.

57
00:05:31,911 --> 00:05:33,467
I have pulled it off before.

58
00:05:33,501 --> 00:05:34,471
Clark,

59
00:05:36,011 --> 00:05:38,658
met U. Is not like smallville high.

60
00:05:38,708 --> 00:05:41,687
It's a much bigger stage.
There's gonna be much bigger problems.

61
00:05:41,754 --> 00:05:45,458
You always told me not to walk away
from something just because it's a challenge.

62
00:05:47,466 --> 00:05:49,073
Dad, I can do this.

63
00:05:49,140 --> 00:05:51,455
I know that you can handle it.

64
00:05:52,509 --> 00:05:56,676
I also know you'll behave yourself this weekend...
stay clear of the beer kegs.

65
00:05:56,743 --> 00:05:58,668
Don't worry. Alcohol can't
affect me, remember?

66
00:05:58,840 --> 00:06:01,501
That's not the point.
You're still underage.

67
00:06:04,447 --> 00:06:07,783
Look, son, I just don't want you
to get booted out before you get in.

68
00:06:07,833 --> 00:06:09,071
- All right?
- Okay.

69
00:06:09,121 --> 00:06:10,644
Now, there's one more thing.

70
00:06:10,695 --> 00:06:12,803
It's very important.

71
00:06:13,071 --> 00:06:15,586
This is a once-in-a-lifetime experience.

72
00:06:15,838 --> 00:06:17,377
Have a great time.

73
00:06:18,248 --> 00:06:19,704
Clark kent...

74
00:06:20,122 --> 00:06:22,654
future met U. Hall of famer?

75
00:06:23,926 --> 00:06:25,299
Hey.

76
00:06:25,851 --> 00:06:28,160
What's the teflon tailback
doing back in town?

77
00:06:28,218 --> 00:06:29,641
Hey, mr. Kent.

78
00:06:29,741 --> 00:06:32,056
Coach calloway wanted to surprise clark,

79
00:06:32,106 --> 00:06:34,148
send a local boy to pick him up.

80
00:06:34,181 --> 00:06:39,386
Well, it definitely worked. I would've never expected to see
the bulldogs' all-time leading rusher in my barn.

81
00:06:39,420 --> 00:06:41,821
Hey, I'm no different than you, clark. I'm just...

82
00:06:41,867 --> 00:06:44,152
a farm boy who happens
to be a decent football player.

83
00:06:44,230 --> 00:06:45,803
"Decent football player".

84
00:06:45,858 --> 00:06:49,440
You're on your way to the nfl,
and you're quite the legend at smallville high.

85
00:06:49,490 --> 00:06:53,428
Yeah, well,your boy broke my record
for single season T.D.S.

86
00:06:53,478 --> 00:06:55,052
Yeah...

87
00:06:55,470 --> 00:06:57,311
You got what it takes, clark.

88
00:06:58,499 --> 00:07:00,144
You really think so?

89
00:07:00,194 --> 00:07:01,851
I know so.

90
00:07:02,286 --> 00:07:05,567
You got a heckuva ride a head of you,
but the thing that's gonna keep you level-headed

91
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:08,094
is remembering where you come from...

92
00:07:08,476 --> 00:07:10,535
like smallville high.

93
00:07:11,037 --> 00:07:12,878
You wanna go say hi to coach quigley?

94
00:07:12,928 --> 00:07:13,982
Sure.

95
00:07:21,116 --> 00:07:24,681
He was no prince charming,
but nobody deserves to have that happen to them.

96
00:07:24,732 --> 00:07:27,393
He can't even speak.
I feel terrible.

97
00:07:27,443 --> 00:07:33,219
Lois, it doesn't take an M.D. to know that a kick
to the gut is not gonna cause head-to-toe paralysis.

98
00:07:33,286 --> 00:07:37,420
I hope the judge agrees. Otherwise, I'm gonna be
the star of my very own woman in prison movie.

99
00:07:37,470 --> 00:07:39,161
How did you post bail?

100
00:07:39,244 --> 00:07:43,985
Four very good friends of mine...
visa, mastercard, american express, and discover.

101
00:07:44,136 --> 00:07:46,379
Chloe, I didn't know where else to go.

102
00:07:46,412 --> 00:07:50,051
And lucky for you,I'm on my way to met U.
For my financial aid pitch.

103
00:07:50,099 --> 00:07:53,245
Why don't we just, um,round-trip together,
and we'll figure this thing out?

104
00:07:53,296 --> 00:07:55,204
Lois, I heard what happened.

105
00:07:55,254 --> 00:07:57,385
I see news travels fast.

106
00:07:57,451 --> 00:07:59,560
The guy you put in the hospital

107
00:07:59,627 --> 00:08:01,133
is geoff's roommate.

108
00:08:01,234 --> 00:08:06,213
Clark, I swear to god, all I did was knock the wind
out of him. I couldn't have paralyzed him.

109
00:08:06,263 --> 00:08:07,936
You were drinking, right?

110
00:08:07,987 --> 00:08:12,706
Those days are over. No more alcohol.
And that includes cough syrup and rum cakes.

111
00:08:14,648 --> 00:08:16,243
Aspirin, anyone?

112
00:08:16,410 --> 00:08:19,356
"Torch" desk drawer on the left-hand side.

113
00:08:21,917 --> 00:08:25,367
Listen, chloe, I know that we were supposed to
drive to met U. Today, but since geoff is here,

114
00:08:25,417 --> 00:08:29,986
I understand. Star quarterback...
you don't wanna ride with the common folk.

115
00:08:30,036 --> 00:08:31,526
You know
it's not like that

116
00:08:31,559 --> 00:08:32,580
It's fine, clark.

117
00:08:33,556 --> 00:08:35,364
Hey, uh, clark,

118
00:08:35,447 --> 00:08:38,677
I'm actually kind of surprised
that you took the football route.

119
00:08:39,866 --> 00:08:41,205
Why?

120
00:08:41,322 --> 00:08:42,426
Well...

121
00:08:42,987 --> 00:08:46,552
I don't know, it just seems like you have kind of
an unfair advantage.

122
00:08:50,126 --> 00:08:51,498
What do you mean?

123
00:08:51,833 --> 00:08:54,929
Well, you have all of
these truly amazing talents,

124
00:08:54,980 --> 00:08:57,808
um, you know,on the field...

125
00:08:59,010 --> 00:09:02,541
well, you know, that's the way it is in sports.
Some people are betterthan others.

126
00:09:04,365 --> 00:09:05,704
Right.

127
00:09:06,139 --> 00:09:09,675
I guess I just don't understand
as much as I thought I did.

128
00:09:11,148 --> 00:09:12,721
About football.

129
00:09:13,006 --> 00:09:14,596
Chloe...

130
00:09:14,981 --> 00:09:18,524
let's go, C.K.
The festivities are about to begin.

131
00:09:29,135 --> 00:09:31,478
I take it you've contemplated my job offer.

132
00:09:31,528 --> 00:09:33,319
It wasn't a hard decision to make.

133
00:09:33,888 --> 00:09:38,122
I forgot to mention, a company car is included
as well as a generous expense account.

134
00:09:38,172 --> 00:09:42,213
I'm not gonna work for somebody whose
mission it is is to break me and my girlfriend up.

135
00:09:43,887 --> 00:09:45,125
Jason...

136
00:09:45,929 --> 00:09:49,142
my only concern is lana's welfare.

137
00:09:50,905 --> 00:09:53,365
But you're not the threat
I'm worried about.

138
00:09:54,369 --> 00:09:56,036
It's your mother.

139
00:09:57,626 --> 00:10:04,622
Did you ever find it strange that every summer as a child
she took you on treks to the far reaches of the globe?

140
00:10:04,772 --> 00:10:07,810
Destinations where there
wasn't even running water.

141
00:10:08,496 --> 00:10:10,572
My mother likes to travel.
She always has.

142
00:10:10,639 --> 00:10:12,664
Those weren't vacations, Jason.

143
00:10:12,848 --> 00:10:15,208
They were research trips...

144
00:10:15,375 --> 00:10:19,807
investigating a woman
who was burned at the stake 400 years ago.

145
00:10:21,175 --> 00:10:23,038
Margaret isabelle theroux?

146
00:10:23,588 --> 00:10:26,882
The countess whose spirit
possessed your girlfriend.

147
00:10:27,185 --> 00:10:31,910
And the fact that it happened soon after you
and your mother came into lana's life, well...

148
00:10:31,960 --> 00:10:33,537
that bothers me.

149
00:10:33,588 --> 00:10:35,056
That bothers me a lot.

150
00:10:35,094 --> 00:10:37,152
I had nothing to do with that.

151
00:10:37,487 --> 00:10:40,165
I would never put lana in jeopardy.

152
00:10:40,215 --> 00:10:43,864
And I believe you,
or I wouldn't offer you this job.

153
00:10:44,232 --> 00:10:46,767
What exactly is it that you want me to do?

154
00:10:50,265 --> 00:10:52,976
I have deep pockets,jason.

155
00:10:53,260 --> 00:10:57,998
Vast resources.
But the one thing I don't have is access.

156
00:10:58,969 --> 00:11:03,873
Two women in your life are somehow intimately
connected to margaret isabelle theroux.

157
00:11:04,124 --> 00:11:07,152
I want you to find out everything they know.

158
00:11:08,056 --> 00:11:10,383
So, what, you want me to spy on them?

159
00:11:11,286 --> 00:11:14,349
How you get the information is up to you.

160
00:11:18,167 --> 00:11:20,158
Now I need an answer.

161
00:11:31,747 --> 00:11:32,969
Coop.

162
00:11:33,505 --> 00:11:35,396
Can you hear me?

163
00:11:39,232 --> 00:11:42,077
It's lois,
your, um, drinking buddy.

164
00:11:43,086 --> 00:11:48,241
I am so sorry this happened to you,
but I swear to god, I didn't do it.

165
00:11:52,308 --> 00:11:56,503
Last night, I would've given anything
to shut him up. And now...

166
00:11:56,989 --> 00:12:01,072
come on, lois. We gotta get outta
here before someone sees you.

167
00:12:02,818 --> 00:12:06,316
Maybe someone close to coop
knows something we don'T.

168
00:12:07,086 --> 00:12:08,693
Lois, I...

169
00:12:09,278 --> 00:12:14,036
I don't think that grandma betty from topeka
is gonna have the answer.

170
00:12:15,285 --> 00:12:17,160
But his girlfriend monique might.

171
00:12:17,227 --> 00:12:18,917
How do you know it's his girlfriend?

172
00:12:18,967 --> 00:12:23,084
When the card ends with "I'll love you forever
and ever," it's a bit of a giveaway.

173
00:12:25,054 --> 00:12:27,547
The girls of Alpha Alpha Alpha
Hope you get well soon!

174
00:12:36,794 --> 00:12:40,208
This truck looks likeit can do everything
but take off and fly.

175
00:12:40,392 --> 00:12:42,702
Hey, check it out. You hit this button...

176
00:12:42,735 --> 00:12:48,282
the operator's there to help you out with whatever you need...
atm locations, movie times, you name it.

177
00:12:48,482 --> 00:12:49,989
That's pretty cool.

178
00:12:50,290 --> 00:12:53,102
Yeah, I hear next year's model is even sweeter.

179
00:12:53,436 --> 00:12:55,830
Unless you want something sportier.

180
00:12:56,776 --> 00:13:00,240
What, you're saying I get a truck like this
if I come here to play?

181
00:13:00,859 --> 00:13:05,529
Let's just say certain alumni are nice enough
to loan their athletes rides.

182
00:13:08,082 --> 00:13:11,178
Clark, college football is big business.

183
00:13:11,580 --> 00:13:14,760
I mean, you get a lot,
but they expect a lot in return.

184
00:13:15,245 --> 00:13:17,203
You have to be better than good.

185
00:13:19,001 --> 00:13:21,461
You have to be a hero out there.

186
00:13:30,086 --> 00:13:33,199
Yeah, I thought you might want to see
where you're gonna be spending your saturdays.

187
00:13:45,467 --> 00:13:55,811
Clark kent, quarterback
he's a bulldog, that's a fact

188
00:13:56,133 --> 00:13:58,075
Clark kent, quarterback...

189
00:13:58,150 --> 00:14:02,300
Ladies and gentlemen, playing quarterback
for your metropolis bulldogs,

190
00:14:02,311 --> 00:14:06,445
from smallville, kansas...
number 8, clark kent!

191
00:14:06,796 --> 00:14:08,324
It's pretty cool, huh?

192
00:14:08,391 --> 00:14:12,299
That's an understatement.
Get used to it, buddy. It's just the beginning.

193
00:14:12,358 --> 00:14:15,069
The golden arm of kansas has arrived.
It's a pleasure to meet you, son.

194
00:14:15,102 --> 00:14:16,793
Coach, it's a pleasure to meet you.

195
00:14:16,818 --> 00:14:19,498
I know a lot of other schools
are coming at you, clark.

196
00:14:19,531 --> 00:14:22,744
But you go with met U.,
And you're gonna win a national championship.

197
00:14:22,811 --> 00:14:24,502
Sounds good to me.

198
00:14:24,753 --> 00:14:26,527
Try this on for size.

199
00:14:26,912 --> 00:14:28,072
Coach,

200
00:14:28,122 --> 00:14:29,327
thanks.

201
00:14:29,930 --> 00:14:33,076
I know you're gonna make
the right decision, son.

202
00:14:36,624 --> 00:14:39,275
Clark, gary bergen... metro motors.

203
00:14:39,325 --> 00:14:43,175
On behalf of the bulldog booster club,
welcome to met U.

204
00:14:43,225 --> 00:14:48,078
If there is anything that you need,
you know where to call.

205
00:14:52,773 --> 00:14:55,434
Everybody wants a winning team, clark...

206
00:14:55,468 --> 00:14:57,828
it's guys like me and you
that make it happen.

207
00:14:59,167 --> 00:15:00,941
Waw, this is amazing.

208
00:15:00,991 --> 00:15:04,104
Dude, you haven't seen nothing yet.

209
00:15:10,922 --> 00:15:12,462
Hi, clark!

210
00:15:13,701 --> 00:15:16,696
The tri alphas are big football fans.

211
00:15:16,747 --> 00:15:18,136
Yeah?

212
00:15:18,755 --> 00:15:24,421
So, we did a little detective work and found out
that your favorite flavor was chocolate.

213
00:15:24,455 --> 00:15:26,513
So we made you cake.

214
00:15:26,547 --> 00:15:29,509
Why, you didn't have to go
through all that trouble.

215
00:15:29,543 --> 00:15:33,414
Anything we can do to help you
commit to met U., Clark.

216
00:15:34,569 --> 00:15:36,711
How about a tour of the house?

217
00:15:41,205 --> 00:15:43,815
Go ahead, C.K. Take your time.

218
00:15:43,866 --> 00:15:46,008
I'll see you back at the dorm.

219
00:15:53,630 --> 00:15:55,421
So you two roommates?

220
00:15:55,471 --> 00:15:57,446
Um... no.

221
00:15:57,998 --> 00:16:00,676
My roommate's on her way
to visit coop at the hospital.

222
00:16:00,710 --> 00:16:02,389
He's her boyfriend.

223
00:16:04,179 --> 00:16:05,719
Clark?

224
00:16:05,769 --> 00:16:08,062
From what we hear...

225
00:16:08,882 --> 00:16:11,348
not only do you have an incredible arm,

226
00:16:11,398 --> 00:16:13,641
you've got great hands.

227
00:16:15,248 --> 00:16:18,746
Really?
Somebody said that to you about me?

228
00:16:19,499 --> 00:16:20,960
Clark...

229
00:16:21,864 --> 00:16:24,776
um, you've got a great view out this window.

230
00:16:24,826 --> 00:16:27,956
Yeah,
if you like brick walls.

231
00:16:29,634 --> 00:16:33,450
Let me show you
an even better view.

232
00:16:35,542 --> 00:16:37,935
I meant the ivy.

233
00:16:39,631 --> 00:16:41,438
What was that?

234
00:16:47,129 --> 00:16:49,003
Let me go check it out.

235
00:16:58,178 --> 00:17:00,187
Uh... some sweaters fell down...

236
00:17:00,237 --> 00:17:01,710
in there.

237
00:17:01,777 --> 00:17:04,304
Um, could I... could I get something to drink?

238
00:17:04,359 --> 00:17:05,726
Um...

239
00:17:06,032 --> 00:17:08,174
yeah. Sure.

240
00:17:13,418 --> 00:17:15,259
And maybe something to eat?

241
00:17:21,871 --> 00:17:23,566
Lois, what are you doing here?

